caption: Figure 3: Approximation error/wallclock time for a variety of distributional RL methods, discount factors, numbers of atoms, and numbers of environment samples.
description: This figure compares the performance of various distributional reinforcement learning algorithms (DCFP, QDP, CDP) across different settings.  The x-axis represents either the number of samples per state or wall-clock time, and the y-axis shows the approximation error (Wasserstein distance).  Different plots show the results for varying discount factors (γ), numbers of atoms (m), and algorithms.
